diff:1377654842:1377640973:=9d8%0a%3c **[[#Law|Laws]]%0a156,169c155%0a%3c !!New Arcadia Laws%0a%3c [[#Law]]%0a%3c Sprawling New Arcadia is filled to the brim with its own internal intrigues, competitions, and politics but the Laws are simple.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1. No Violence within Market Squares or Shops.%0a%3c 2. Honor Your Deals.%0a%3c 3. Citizens and Residents are required to serve the city militia if New Arcadia comes under external attack. %0a%3c %0a%3c Beyond those three Laws, New Arcadia is ruled by those with the strength to hold it. Even the Laws themselves are held sacrosanct not because of any pledge but because those with the strength to enforce them do so. Not even the worst scum of the outer circle would lift a hand in violence against a sworn enemy while within a Market Square or else everyone would turn against them. Their word would no longer be trusted, merchants would no longer deal with them, and they would eventually need to leave New Arcadia or find a way to start a different life in order to survive. When an accusation that someone has broken the Laws comes up with no clear Truth to the situation, the dispute will often find itself in the lap of whoever the local Leader is. It may be a Merchant Prince of the Upper Circle who owns the neighborhood and maintains HOA style standards, or it could be a slum lord gangster who collected 'protection money' from the area. %0a%3c %0a%3c It is generally ideal to settle such disputes at the lowest level possible instead of calling upon higher and higher powers within the city to intervene as they will all be expecting favors for ruling in a particular direction. On rare occassion a dispute might find itself to the halls of Lord Flint's labyrinth at the center of the city but whomever he rules against is more likely to serve as a mid afternoon snack than have the chance to leave the city in one piece.%0a%3c [[#LawEnd]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Society Content%0a---%0a> !!Society Content%0a
