diff:1377588157:1377585812:=14,15c14%0a%3c **[[#HouseRules|HouseRules]]%0a%3c **[[#Creation|Creation]]%0a---%0a> **[[#CtL-Blah|Blah]]%0a299,354c298%0a%3c [[#FreeholdEnd]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Venue Content%0a%3c !!House Rules%0a%3c [[#HouseRules]]%0a%3c *'''Autumn Mantle 1:''' The Mantle bonus provides a character one bonus die to oneiromancy rolls instead of the RAW 2 dice bonus to contract activations using Occult.  %0a%3c *'''Frailties:''' A changeling may receive a frailty in place of a derangement upon losing a dot of Clarity. %0a%3c *'''Cultivation of Hedge Bounty:''' Requires a Hollow. 2x Hollow Size types of Fruit, Oddments, or Trifles may be cultivated. %0a%3c *'''Glamour:''' Glamour anchors a changeling in the fae world and creatures of the Hedge and Arcadia can more easily detect a changeling brimming with glamour in reserve.%0a%3c **75%25- 100%25 gives a +3 bonus to True Fae and hobs to detect the changeling. In addition, changelings are more likely to anthropomorphize the world around them when full of glamour.%0a%3c **25%25-75%25 gives neither bonus or penalty.%0a%3c **0%25-25%25 gives a -5 penalty to True Fae and hobs to detect the changeling. %0a%3c *'''Dual Kith:''' The merit in Rites of Spring will be used. After character creation addition kiths may (if you’re lucky or create your own luck) be for sale at the Goblin Market. Kiths may also be sold at the Market.%0a%3c *'''Hedgespinning''': With one dot, all Hedgespun weapons begin at the basic stats for their type; size, durability, damage, applicability for fighting styles and so on. Furthe dots can then add to the weapon’s abilities as noted in Rites of Spring.%0a%3c *'''Toxicity''': Each dot gives +2 Toxicity. Only two may be purchased, for any given weapon, for a total Toxicity of 4. %0a%3c %0a%3c !!Alternative Rules in Effect%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Seasonal Affiliation, RoS pg 27:''' A changeling's seasonal affiliation is determined by the season in which he or she escaped Arcadia, or perhaps the season he or she escapes during is determined by his or her seasonal affiliation. A mantle is thus not just a political affiliation but an inherent mark of a changeling's freedom from their Keeper. Mantles may be shed with similar difficulty to shedding a kith, but being courtless is a mark of being mentally unstable at best and a likely loyalist. %0a%3c %0a%3c '''True Names, RoS pg. 23:''' Using the target of a Contract’s True Name always works as the catch for any contract that is designed to be used on a single target. This cannot be used to target oneself. True Names can be changed as per the first option on page 24. %0a%3c %0a%3c '''Reaping Glamour, RoS pg. 28:''' Glamour can be drained from fae creatures with a touch and a Wits+Wyrd vs. Resolve+Wyrd roll. Each success steals one point of glamour.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Clarity Benefits and Drawbacks, RoS pg. 75:''' Clarity 8+ offers several bonuses related to perception, and penalties for Clarity every two points below 7.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Counseling, RoS pg. 81:''' Psychiatric help can make it easier to improve your Clarity.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Shared Dreams, SaD pg. 107-8:''' Motleys whose members all have an Empathy (Oneiromancy) specialty may take advantage of the Shared Dreams mechanics.%0a%3c [[#HouseRulesEnd]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Character Creation%0a%3c [[#Creation]]%0a%3c !!!Attributes and Skills%0a%3c * '''Attribute 5 %25red%25(3)'''%25%25: This overrides the general character creation rule of 1 restricted slot for each dot 4 and higher. Strength 4 costs 1 restricted slot. Strength 5 costs 3 restricted slots.%0a%3c * '''Skill 5 %25red%25(3)'''%25%25: This overrides the general character creation rule of 1 restricted slot for each dot 4 and higher. Brawl 4 costs 1 restricted slot. Brawl 5 costs 3 restricted slots.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Merits%0a%3c * '''Merit 5 %25red%25(3)'''%25%25: This overrides the general character creation rule of 1 restricted slot for each dot 4 and higher.%0a%3c *'''Dual-kith %25red%25(2 or 3)'''%25%25''': In-Seeming Kiths take 2 restricted slots. Out-of-Seeming Kiths take 3 restricted slots.%0a%3c *'''Mantle 3 %25red%25(1)'''%25%25: Note that both Mantle and Court Goodwill dots may be lost if a character acts in such a way as would be unfit.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Contracts%0a%3c *'''Directional, Dusk, Dawn court Contracts''': Available if prerequisites are met. (Books: Dancers in Dusk, Winter Masques, Swords at Dawn)%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Traits%0a%3c *'''Clarity 6- %25red%25(1 per dot)'''%25%25''': As with Morality (General Character Creation), Clarity can be dropped at Character Creation for 5XP each time. %0a%3c *'''Wyrd 3 %25red%25(1)'''%25%25%0a%3c *'''Wyrd 4 %25red%25(3)'''%25%25%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Banned Items%0a%3c * Goblin Merchant Merits are currently unavailable to players.%0a%3c * Cambions and Fae-Touched characters are currently unavailable for play.%0a%3c * Unwitting Pledges are unavailable.%0a%3c * Directional, Dusk and Dawn court characters are not available for play.%0a%3c [[#CreationEnd]]%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a---%0a> [[#FreeholdEnd]]%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
